# Bōkendokei Project Overview

## Project Purpose

Bōkendokei is a habit-tracking adventure game where users "Keep track of your adventures. Get loot. Buy gear." The core vision is to make habit formation fun and engaging through gamification.

## Tech Stack

-   **Frontend**: Next.js 15 + React 19 + TypeScript
-   **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
-   **Build Tool**: Turbopack enabled
-   **Linting**: ESLint with Next.js config
-   **Path Aliases**: `@/*` maps to workspace root

## Project Structure

-   Main app entry: [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx)
-   App layout: [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx)
-   Global styles: [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
-   Documentation: [doc/bokendokei.md](mdc:doc/bokendokei.md), [doc/look.md](mdc:doc/look.md)
-   Configuration: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json), [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts)

## Development Commands

-   `yarn dev` - Start development server with Turbopack
-   `yarn build` - Build for production with Turbopack
-   `yarn lint` - Run ESLint

## Key Principles

-   Make habit formation fun through gamification
-   Focus on MVP features first
-   Use modern React patterns (React 19)
-   Maintain clean TypeScript code
-   Follow Next.js 15 best practices
